# Quote App

A simple web application for managing quotes. This application is built using Node.js, Express, MongoDB, and EJS as the templating engine. It includes user authentication and session management with Passport.js.

## Features

- User authentication with registration and login.
- Session management using express-session and Passport.js.
- Manage quotes with basic CRUD operations.
- User-friendly interface with EJS templates.

## Prerequisites

Ensure you have the following installed on your system:

- [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/) (version 14.x or higher recommended)
- [MongoDB](https://www.mongodb.com/try/download/community) (running on default port 27017)
- A `.env` file with the necessary environment variables

## Getting Started

### Installation

1. Clone the repository:

   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/yourusername/quote-app.git
   cd quote-app


Install the dependencies:npm install
Set up your .env file with the following variables
PORT=2345
DB_URL=mongodb+srv://<username>:<password>@cluster0.lqes229.mongodb.net/?retryWrites=true&w=majority&appName=Cluster0
DB_PASSWORD=<your_db_password>
SECRET=<your_secret_key>


Replace <username> with your MongoDB username.
Replace <password> with your MongoDB password.
Replace <your_db_password> with your actual MongoDB password.
Replace <your_secret_key> with your session secret key.

Run the application: nodemon index.js



quote-app/
│
├── public/                 # Static files (CSS, JS, images)
├── routes/                 # Express routes
│   ├── auth.js             # Authentication routes
│   └── quote.js            # Quote management routes
│
├── views/                  # EJS templates
│   ├── index.ejs           # Home page
│   ├── register.ejs        # Registration page
│   ├── login.ejs           # Login page
│   └── submit.ejs          # Submit quote page
│
├── .env                    # Environment variables
├── index.js                # Main server file
├── package.json            # Node.js dependencies and scripts
└── README.md               # Project documentation



